HEADWORD: Histogenesis
<hw>His`to*gen"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"isto`s</grk> tissue + E. <ets>genesis</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The formation and development of
organic tissues; histogeny; -- the opposite of
<xex>histolysis</xex>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Germ history of cells,
and of the tissues composed of cells.</def>
<rj><au>Haeckel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

